  "Earthquakes never affect areas with granite bedrock when evaluated systematically": "",
  "Sandy soil is too expensive to build on, particularly regarding transmitting according to conventional analysis": "",
  "Sandy, water-saturated soil near rivers is highly susceptible to liquefaction and amplifies seismic waves, increasing both shaking intensity and ground failure risk. Solid bedrock is far more stable, transmitting seismic waves without amplifying them and providing firm support for foundations.": "",
  "Chile experienced a M8.8 earthquake in 2010 that was hundreds of times more powerful than Haiti's M7.0 earthquake the same year. Yet Chile had 525 deaths compared to Haiti's estimated 200,000+. What factors explain this dramatic difference in casualties?": "",
