  "Chile's earthquake occurred in an unpopulated area, particularly regarding public under the given assumptions": "",
  "Chile's drastically lower death toll despite a far more powerful earthquake demonstrates that preparedness saves lives. Chile's strict building codes (developed from experience with frequent earthquakes), emergency planning, and public awareness resulted in far fewer casualties than Haiti, which lacked these protections.": ""
